latestIgtvVideos.title: How to do Supported shoulder stand/ Sarvangasana #colladiyetyoga
latestIgtvVideos.caption:
Hello all! Here goes asana no. 3!!
Correction: *Savasana **Keep your toes pointed, knees straight, try your best to make a perfect straight line. ❤️Personal tip: When nobody is available to watch if you are doing yoga in a good form, always do it front of a mirror to keep a check. Or if you don't have a long mirror, you can take a video which you can watch later and correct your mistakes 😊

Benefits:☑️ Lung capacity is increased as the diaphragm, which is the muscle of respiration, has to work against gravity in this posture, this helps in the abdominal respiration☑️ Stagnant blood from the lower regions of the body is drained to the heart improving the supply of fresh blood to these parts and the whole circulatory system☑️Prevents varicose veins☑️It releases the normal gravitational pressure from the anus muscles which helps with haemorrhoids ☑️Helps to balance the mood and calms your mind☑️ Beneficial to female reproductive system due to increased blood flow to pelvis.☑️Stretches the shoulders, neck ☑️ Tones legs and buttocks. ❌❌Contraindications: High blood pressure, heart/brain diseases.
During menstruation and pregnancy. Should be avoided if suffering from a very enlarged thyroid, enlarged spleen or liver as well as cervical spondylitis, slipped disc, headache and weak blood vessels in the eyes.

UTTANASANA / STANDING FORWARD BEND POSE.

Beginners can hold onto a stool or chair in front of them to help bend at 90degrees at hip joint.

BENEFITS: Strengthens the thigh and knees, stretches hamstrings, calves and hips. Calms the the brain and helps relieve stress, anxiety. Improves digestion.
